00:31:29.292 --> 00:31:30.500
AUDIENCE: Hi, my name is Pat.

00:31:30.500 --> 00:31:33.140
I work here on Google Maps.

00:31:33.140 --> 00:31:35.990
So I guess my question is,
a lot of the conversation

00:31:35.990 --> 00:31:37.850
is focused around
the Middle East.

00:31:37.850 --> 00:31:41.480
Are there any scenarios
happening outside of the Middle

00:31:41.480 --> 00:31:42.872
East that you work with--

00:31:42.872 --> 00:31:44.330
I think you said
for Rainbow Street

00:31:44.330 --> 00:31:46.820
you're specifically focused
on Lebanon and Jordan--

00:31:46.820 --> 00:31:51.200
but anything that we should
know about issues outside

00:31:51.200 --> 00:31:52.990
of that part of the
world, especially

00:31:52.990 --> 00:31:57.054
I guess with the recent
news coming out of Chechnya?

00:31:57.054 --> 00:31:57.970
LARA FINKBEINER: Yeah.

00:31:57.970 --> 00:32:00.851
So IRAP, I say we're Middle
East focused because that's

00:32:00.851 --> 00:32:02.850
primarily where the
majority of our clients are,

00:32:02.850 --> 00:32:06.530
but we provide almost all
of our assistance remotely.

00:32:06.530 --> 00:32:10.130
And so we work with folks
all around the world.

00:32:10.130 --> 00:32:12.500
And I'll speak about
Chechnya in just a moment,

00:32:12.500 --> 00:32:14.510
but I guess the thing
I would emphasize here

00:32:14.510 --> 00:32:16.070
is a lot of what we're talking
about in the Middle East

00:32:16.070 --> 00:32:18.960
plays out in all these different
regions around the world.

00:32:18.960 --> 00:32:20.390
Whether you're
fleeing from Uganda

00:32:20.390 --> 00:32:21.980
to a neighboring
country, or if you're

00:32:21.980 --> 00:32:24.590
trying to leave Chechnya and
go to a neighboring country,

00:32:24.590 --> 00:32:26.600
again, even crossing
an international border

00:32:26.600 --> 00:32:30.627
doesn't necessarily make
you safe as an LGBT person.

00:32:30.627 --> 00:32:32.210
And actually, I talk
about this a lot,

00:32:32.210 --> 00:32:33.230
but I actually think
there needs to be

00:32:33.230 --> 00:32:35.870
a lot more sort of direct
pipelines from your country

00:32:35.870 --> 00:32:40.220
of origin to a safe country if
you're LGBT because sometimes

00:32:40.220 --> 00:32:41.840
you're even safer
in your own country

00:32:41.840 --> 00:32:44.298
because you might have some
networks or some people you can

00:32:44.298 --> 00:32:46.100
rely on if things
go really south,

00:32:46.100 --> 00:32:48.590
or maybe you continue
working and making an income.

00:32:48.590 --> 00:32:50.381
All of those things
are taken away from you

00:32:50.381 --> 00:32:51.970
when you flee your country.

00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:54.950
But it's basically playing
out all over the world.

00:32:54.950 --> 00:32:58.622
Most of the hotspots where
you see LGBT persecution,

00:32:58.622 --> 00:33:00.830
things are not a lot better
in neighboring countries,

00:33:00.830 --> 00:33:04.500
which are the only places
that can really access.

00:33:04.500 --> 00:33:07.610
In regards to
Chechnya, the situation

00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:09.920
has gotten a lot
of attention, which

00:33:09.920 --> 00:33:12.650
has been really important.

00:33:12.650 --> 00:33:16.250
We actually have seen a
number of countries step up,

00:33:16.250 --> 00:33:19.040
and we've gotten
some folks to safety

00:33:19.040 --> 00:33:20.330
in other European countries.

00:33:20.330 --> 00:33:22.913
And we're in talks of trying to
help people come to the United

00:33:22.913 --> 00:33:23.820
States as well.

00:33:23.820 --> 00:33:26.390
So there actually has
been an encouraging sort

00:33:26.390 --> 00:33:28.550
of international
response to that,

00:33:28.550 --> 00:33:33.290
which is really great
because what's going on there

00:33:33.290 --> 00:33:35.030
right now is just deplorable.

00:33:35.030 --> 00:33:37.280
So yeah, to answer your
question, we are definitely

00:33:37.280 --> 00:33:39.321
are involved in other
areas of the world as well.

00:33:43.320 --> 00:33:45.750
KEVIN STEEN: I think for Rainbow
